Linked List Specific methods (these methods are not declared in Collection or List interface), to use this methods we cannot upcast
This is until (java 21 v) , after this they have added the these LinkedList specific method in 'List (interface)' , after 21 v we can upcast and use

addFirst(E e)	void	Inserts element at the beginning (head).
addLast(E e)		void	Inserts element at the end (tail).
getFirst()		E	Returns the first element (head) without removing.
getLast()		E	Returns the last element (tail) without removing.
removeFirst()		E	Removes and returns the first element.
removeLast()		E	Removes and returns the last element.
offerFirst(E e)		boolean	Inserts element at front; returns true if successful.
offerLast(E e)		boolean	Inserts element at end; returns true if successful.
pollFirst()		E	Retrieves and removes first element, or returns null if empty.
pollLast()		E	Retrieves and removes last element, or returns null if empty.
peekFirst()		E	Retrieves but does not remove first element, or returns null if empty.
peekLast()		E	Retrieves but does not remove last element, or returns null if empty.
descendingIterator()	Iterator<E>	Returns an iterator over elements in reverse order.